EnumInfo.Comment: When changing from 1 to 0: the maximum drive off delay time (IDN S-0-0273) is started, drive is decelerated as best as possible according to the emergency stop deceleration (IDN S-0-0429), followed by disabling of the torque at n min, after the drive off delay time (IDN S-0-0207). The power stage can remain in an activated state (only possible when bit 14=1). After the maximum drive off delay time (IDN S-0-0273) is elapsed, the locking of brake is initiated and the torque is disabled.
When changing from 0 to 1: drive follows the command values of the control unit after the drive on delay time (IDN S-0-0206).

Object.Name: Control unit cycle time (TNcyc)
Object.Comment: The control unit cycle time defines the cyclic intervals during which the control unit makes new command values available. It is defined as 62us, 125us, 250us, ..., up to 20ms in steps of 250s.

Object.Name: Communication cycle time (tSync)
Object.Comment: The communication cycle time of the interface defines the intervals during which the cyclic data are transferred. It is defined as 62us, 125us, 250us, ..., up to 20ms in steps of 250s.

Object.Name: Class 1 diagnostic (C1D)
Object.Comment:
Drive shut-down error.

A drive error situation of class C1D leads to the following:

  • A best case deceleration followed by torque release at nmin.
  • The drive shut-down error bit for C1D is set to '1' in the drive status (bit 13). The error bit is reset to '0' by the drive only when no errors of C1D exists and after the command 'reset class 1 diagnostic' (IDN S-0-0099) has been received by the drive.

Object.Name: Class 2 diagnostic (C2D)
Object.Comment: Shut-down warning (warning) When a warning is activated or canceled in the C2D, this sets the change bit for C2D in the drive status (bit 12) to a binary 1. When the C2D is read via the parameter channel, the C2D change bit is canceled and reset to 0.

Object.Name: Telegram type
Object.Comment: The telegram type allows selection between standard telegrams and application telegrams.

Object.Name: Configuration list of AT
Object.Comment: This IDN list contains the IDNs whose operation data will be transmitted cyclically in the AT in an application telegram. Only operation data which are present in the "IDN list of configurable data in the AT" (IDN S-0-0187) are allowed as cyclic AT data.

Object.Name: IDN-list of all operation data
Object.Comment: All IDNs of all operation data, procedure commands, parameters etc. of a given drive are stored in this IDN-list.

Object.Name: IDN-list of operation data for CP2
Object.Comment: IDNs of all operation data needed for CP2 are stored in this IDN-list and must be transferred during CP2. Processing this list is required before switching to CP3.

Object.Name: IDN-list of operation data for CP3
Object.Comment: IDNs of all operation data needed for CP3 are stored in this IDN-list and must be transferred during CP3. Processing this list is required before switching to CP4.

Object.Name: IDN-list of operation data for CP4
Object.Comment: IDNs of all operational data which can be changed during CP4 are stored in this IDN-list.

Object.Name: IDN-list of invalid operation data for CP2
Object.Comment: IDNs which are in the list "IDN-list of operation data for CP2" (IDN S-0-0018) and which are considered invalid by the drive prior to switchover from CP2 (PreOp) to CP3 (SafeOp) are stored in this IDN-list (see IDN S-0-0127).

Object.Name: IDN-list of invalid operation data for CP3
Object.Comment: IDNs which are in the list "IDN-list of operation data for CP3" (IDN S-0-0019) and which are considered invalid by the drive prior to switchover from CP3 (SafeOp) to CP4 (Op) are stored in this IDN-list.

Object.Name: Configuration list of MDT
Object.Comment: This IDN list contains the IDNs whose operation data will be transmitted cyclically in the MDT in an application telegram. Only operation data which are present in the "IDN-list of configurable data in the MDT" (IDN S-0-0188) are allowed as cyclic MDT data.

Object.Name: IDN-list of all procedure commands
Object.Comment: All IDNs of all drive procedure commands are stored in this IDN-list.

Object.Name: MDT error counter
Object.Comment: The MDT error counter counts all invalid MDTs (Master Data Telegramms) in communication phase 4 (Operational).

Object.Name: Manufacturer Version
Object.Comment: The operation data of the manufacturer version contains the actual firmware version and additional information of the device.

Object.Name: Hardware version
Object.Comment: The operation data of the hardware version contains the actual hardware version and additional information of the device.

Object.Name: Primary operation mode
Object.Comment: The Operation Mode (Primary Operation Mode or Secondary Operatin Mode 1 to 3) is selected via bits 9 and 8 in the DriveControlWord word of the MDT. The activated operation mode is indicated by bits 9 and 8 of the DriveStatusWord in the AT. Actual the operation modes 'pos ctrl xxx' can only be choosen as primary operation mode with no secondary operation mode.

Object.Name: Secondary operation mode 1
Object.Comment: The Operation Mode (Primary Operation Mode or Secondary Operatin Mode 1 to 3) is selected via bits 9 and 8 in the DriveControlWord word of the MDT. The activated operation mode is indicated by bits 9 and 8 of the DriveStatusWord in the AT.

Object.Name: Secondary operation mode 2
Object.Comment: The Operation Mode (Primary Operation Mode or Secondary Operation Mode 1 to 3) is selected via bits 9 and 8 in the DriveControlWord word of the MDT. The activated operation mode is indicated by bits 9 and 8 of the DriveStatusWord in the AT.

Object.Name: Secondary operation mode 3
Object.Comment: The Operation Mode (Primary Operation Mode or Secondary Operatin Mode 1 to 3) is selected via bits 9 and 8 in the DriveControlWord word of the MDT. The activated operation mode is indicated by bits 9 and 8 of the DriveStatusWord in the AT.

Object.Name: Velocity command value
Object.Comment: In the velocity control operating mode in the drive, the control unit transfers the velocity command values to the drive in the time pattern of the control unit cycle time.

Object.Name: Additive velocity command value
Object.Comment: The additive velocity command value is an additional velocity offset which is added to the velocity command value.

Object.Name: Velocity feedback value 1
Object.Comment: The velocity feedback value 1 is transferred from the drive to the control unit. The velocity feedback value 1 refers to the motor feedback.

Object.Name: Velocity polarity parameter
Object.Comment: This parameter is used to switch polarities of velocity data for specific applications. Polarities are not switched internally but externally (on the input and output) of a closed loop system. The motor shaft turns clockwise when there is a positive velocity command difference and no inversion is programmed.

Object.Name: Velocity data scaling type
Object.Comment: A variety of scaling methods can be selected by means of the scaling type parameter.

Object.Name: Velocity data scaling factor
Object.Comment:
This parameter defines the scaling factor for all velocity data in the drive. The velocity data scaling not changeable and set to the following scaling:
  • 1 Turn/min = 1 rpm = 17895.69707 inc/(1024 * ms)
  • 1 inc/(1024 ms) = 5.587935448e-5 Turn/min

Object.Name: Velocity data scaling exponent
Object.Comment:
This parameter defines the scaling exponent for all velocity data in the drive. The velocity data scaling not changeable and set to the following scaling:
  • 1 Turn/min = 17895.69707 inc/(1024 * ms)
  • 1 inc/(1024 ms) = 5.587935448e-5 Turn/min

Object.Name: Position command value
Object.Comment: During the position control drive operation mode, the position command values are transferred from the control unit to the drive according to the time pattern of the control unit cycle.

Object.Name: Additive position command value
Object.Comment: This IDN is used if an additional position offset is required during position control operation mode in the drive. The additive position command ofset is added to the position command value (IDN S-0-0047).

Object.Name: Position feedback value 1 (motor feedback)
Object.Comment: The position feedback value 1 (motor feedback) displays the actual position of the motor feedback.

Object.Name: Position feedback value 2 (external feedback)
Object.Comment: The position feedback value 2 (additional feedback) displays the actual position of the second feedback.

Object.Name: Position polarity parameters
Object.Comment: This parameter is used to switch polarities of reported position data for specific applications. Polarities are switched outside (i.e., on the input and output) of a closed loop system. The motor shaft turns clockwise (as viewed from the output shaft) when there is a positive position command difference and no inversion is programmed.

Object.Name: Position data scaling type
Object.Comment: A variety of scaling methods can be selected by means of the scaling type parameter.

Object.Name: Rotational position resolution
Object.Comment: This parameter defines the rotational position resolution for all position data in a drive. The rotational position resolution is not changeable and set to 2^20 inc/turn = 1048576 inc/turn.

Object.Comment: The negative acceleration parameter limits the maximum acceleration ability of the drive to the programmed value. If the velocity decreases it is said to be a negative acceleration.

Object.Name: Sercos interface version
Object.Comment: The operation data contains the version of the SERCOS interface specification.

Object.Name: Monitoring window
Object.Comment: When the position error value exceeds the maximum value of the monitoring window, the drive sets an error for excessive position deviation in C1D (S-0-0011).

Object.Name: Acceleration data scaling factor
Object.Comment: This parameter defines the scaling factor for all acceleration data in a drive. This parameter is not changeable and the acceleration data scaling is set to 1/1000 of the 'configured channel peak current' (IDN P-0-0092).

Object.Name: Acceleration data scaling exponent
Object.Comment: This parameter defines the scaling factor for all acceleration data in a drive. This parameter is not changeable and the acceleration data scaling is set to 1/1000 of the 'configured channel peak current' (IDN P-0-0092).

Object.Name: Weight counterbalance
Object.Comment: This parameter is used to program the counterbalance (torque) of vertically positioned (hanging) axes in the positive or negative effective direction.

Object.Name: Probing cycle procedure command (pc)
Object.Comment: When the master sets and enables the probing cycle procedure command, the drive reacts on the following parameters: probe 1/2 enable (IDN S-0-0405/S-0-0406) and probe 1/2 (IDN S-0-0401/S-0-0402) as programmed in the probe control parameter (IDN S-0-0169). While the procedure command is activated, the control unit can start multiple measurements. If the control unit does not want any more measurements, the control unit cancels the procedure command.

Object.Name: Probe status
Object.Comment: If the drive stores one or more measurement values while the procedure command "probing cycle" (IDN S-0-0170) is activated, it simultaneously sets the assigned bit in the probe status. If probe 1 enable (IDN S-0-0405) is reset by the control unit, the drive resets bit 0 and bit 1 of probe status. If probe 2 enable (IDN S-0-0406) is reset by the control unit, the drive resets bit 2 and bit 3 of probe status. The drive resets all bits of the probe status when the control unit cancels the "probing cycle procedure command" (IDN S-0-0170)

Object.Name: Length of the configurable data record in the AT
Object.Comment: The drive indicates the maximum length in bytes which can be processed in the configurable data record of the AT (Amplifier Telegramm) in the operation data of this IDN.

Object.Name: Length of the configurable data record in the MDT
Object.Comment: The drive indicates the maximum length in bytes which can be processed in the configurable data record of the MDT in the operation data of this IDN.

Object.Name: IDN-list of configurable data in the AT
Object.Comment: This list consists of the IDNs of operation data which can be processed by the drive cyclically as output values.

Object.Name: IDN-list of configurable data in the MDT
Object.Comment: This list consists of the IDNs of operation data which can be processed by the drive cyclically as command values.

Object.Name: Following distance
Object.Comment: The actual difference between the commanded position and the actual position is placed in this parameter.

Object.Name: Amplifier warning temperature
Object.Comment: When the amplifier temperature exceeds the amplifier warning temperature value, the drive sets the warning bit for amplifier overtemperature in C2D (IDN S-0-0012).

Object.Name: Motor warning temperature
Object.Comment: When the motor temperature exceeds the motor warning temperature value, the drive sets the warning bit for motor overtemperature in C2D (S-0-0012).

Object.Name: Amplifier shut down temperature
Object.Comment: When the amplifier temperature exceeds the amplifier shut-down temperature value, the drive sets the bit for amplifier overtemperature shut-down in C1D (IDN S-0-0011).

Object.Name: Motor shut down temperature
Object.Comment: When the motor temperature exceeds the motor shut-down temperature value, the drive sets the bit for motor overtemperature shut-down in C1D (IDN S-0-0011).

Object.Name: Drive on delay time
Object.Comment: After torque is activated (bit 14, drive status is set) "drive on delay time" is started. The drive follows the command values after the "drive on delay time" has elapsed.

Object.Name: Drive off delay time
Object.Comment: After "drive off" (bit 15 of the master control word) is reset and n_min is reached, the drive off delay time is started and the locking of the brake is initiated. The torque remains activated in the drive until this drive off delay time is elapsed. The motor brake management uses this time to close the motor brake before the torque/force is switched off.

Object.Name: IDN-list of parameter set
Object.Comment: This list contains all IDNs of parameter set 0 which are also supported in the parameter sets 1 to 7.

Object.Name: Multiplication factor 1
Object.Comment: Multiplication Factor 1 defines the factor that the motor feedback signal is multiplied by in the drive.

Object.Name: Multiplication factor 2
Object.Comment: Multiplication Factor 2 defines the factor that the motor feedback signal is multiplied by in the drive.

Object.Name: Password
Object.Comment: The interface supports passwords that can be used to write protect selected parameters. IDN S-0-0267 is used to enable and disable write protection on password proctected IDNs.

Object.Name: Maximum drive off delay time
Object.Comment: After "drive off" (bit 15, control word) is reset, the maximum drive off delay time is started. After the maximum drive off delay time is elapsed, the locking of the brake is initiated and the torque is disabled independend of the actual motor speed.

Object.Name: Received drive addresses
Object.Comment: The received EtherCAT slave address is displayed.

Object.Name: List of supported operation modes
Object.Comment: In this list the codes of all supported operation modes are displayed.

Object.Name: Drive enable delay time
Object.Comment: When "drive enable" is set (bit 14, control word) the "drive enable delay time" is started.

Object.Name: Velocity feed forward gain
Object.Comment: Velocity feed forward is effective in the operation mode "Position control without following error (lagless)", and serves to reduce the velocity-dependent following error.

Object.Name: Velocity error
Object.Comment: The actual difference between the commanded velocity and actual velocity is placed in this parameter.

Object.Name: Acceleration feed forward gain
Object.Comment: Acceleration feed forward is effective in the operation mode Position control without following distance (lag-less) , and serves to reduce acceleration / deceleration-dependent following distance.

Object.Name: Diagnostic numbers list
Object.Comment: The drive records every change of the diagnostic number into this list. The list is organized as a ring buffer. When the list is read via the parameter channel, the drive will position the last diagnostic recorded as the first element of the list.

Object.Name: DC bus voltage
Object.Comment: The drives DC bus voltage value is placed in this parameter.

Object.Name: DC bus current
Object.Comment: The drive places the measured (actual) DC bus current in this parameter.

Object.Name: Motor temperature
Object.Comment: The drive places the measured (actual) motor temperature in this parameter.

Object.Name: Amplifier temperature
Object.Comment: The drive places the measured (actual) amplifier temperature in this parameter.

Object.Name: Diagnostic number
Object.Comment: For every diagnostic, the drive stores a manufacturer specific code in the diagnostic number parameter.

Object.Name: Probe 1 enable
Object.Comment: This parameter is used to assign an IDN to probe 1 enable. This allows the status "probe 1 enable" to be assigned to a real-time control bit (see IDN S-0-0301). Probe 1 enable is checked by the drive only as long as the procedure command "probing cycle" (IDN S-0-0170) is active. For a new probing cycle with the same edge of probe 1 the control unit has to reset probe 1 enable to "0" and set it to "1" Bit 0 is defined for operation data only.

Object.Name: Probe 1 positive latched
Object.Comment: This parameter is used to assign an IDN to probe 1 positive latched. This allows the status "probe 1 positive latched" to be assigned to a real-time status bit (see S-0-0305). Bit 0 of this parameter is set by the drive only if the procedure command "probing cycle" (S-0-0170) is active, the signal "probe 1 enable" (S-0-0405) is set to 1 and the positive edge of "probe 1" (S-0-0401) is registered. Simultaneously the drive stores the position feedback value in "probe 1 positive edge" (S-0-0130). The drive resets this bit when the control unit cancels the procedure command "probing cycle" or when probe 1 enable is reset to 0. Bit 0 is defined for operation data only. (For more details see S-0-0179.)

Object.Name: Probe 1 negative latched
Object.Comment: This parameter is used to assign an IDN to probe 1 negative latched. This allows the status "probe 1 negative latched" to be assigned a real-time status bit. Bit 0 of this parameter is set by the drive only if the procedure command "probing cycle" (S-0-0170) is active, the signal "probe 1 enable" (S- 0-0405) is set to 1 and the negative edge of "probe 1" (S-0-0401) is registered. Simultaneously the drive stores the position feedback value in "probe 1 negative edge" (S-0-0131). The drive resets this bit when the control unit cancels the procedure command "probing cycle" or when probe 1 enable is reset to 0. Bit 0 is defined for operation data only. (For more details see S-0-0179.)

Object.Name: Serial number drive control
Object.Comment: The serial number of the drive is displayed in this parameter.

Object.Name: Switching frequency of the IGBT module
Object.Comment: This parameter defines the switching frequency of the IGBT module.

Object.Name: Current ctrl cycle time
Object.Comment: This parameter defines the current ctrl looop cycle time.

Object.Name: Velocity ctrl cycle time
Object.Comment: This parameter defines the velocity control loop cycle time.

Object.Name: Position ctrl cycle time
Object.Comment: This parameter defines the position control loop cycle time.

Object.Name: Synchronization mode
Object.Comment: With this IDN is it possible to set the IO-Synchronisation mode. The default is "Use DC's, Watchdog ON, Level 0". In this mode synchronisation problems generate an error. With choosing "Level 1" the error limit is increased. This level should only be used for systems where the IO synchronsation is not stable. This level could not be used if the position interface is configured.
